[src:http-request-smuggling/http-headers-cheat-sheet] In some cases, both header tables may be used, which can result in duplicate headers if the same header is configured in both contexts.
[src:http-request-smuggling/http-headers-cheat-sheet] If a header needs to be removed entirely, it should be unset in both contexts (`onsuccess` and `always`).
